    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant with VarioCam Plus, delivering linear torque across the rev range. Mated to a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle, the drivetrain remains tight with positive engagement. Critically, the IMS bearing and Rear Main Seal have been addressed with documented retrofits, mitigating common failure points. The suspension retains its factory geometry, providing the communicative steering and rear-engine weight bias enthusiasts demand. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with spirited use, the chassis remains rigid and the cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temp thermostat and high-flow water pump. This is a mechanically sound 911 primed for the canyons.",
